Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.05,0:01:47.02,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,The Deduction That Was Too Good
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.99,0:01:50.96,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Beika Street
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.06,0:01:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran... It's this way. This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.26,0:01:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, you always make so much trouble\Nwhen you drink too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.03,0:02:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, next time don't go to the train station\Nif you've had too much to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.03,0:02:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not this again...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.57,0:02:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.11,0:02:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"From 8 PM to 10 PM: Eat and drink as much as you want!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.24,0:02:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.71,0:02:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.02,0:02:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only drank three bottles of beer\Nand ate five plates of appetizers!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.23,0:02:31.46,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Takayoki Eri (25)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.36,0:02:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't throw things around!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.76,0:02:31.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pick it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.66,0:02:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want me to pick it up? You pick it up, you imbecile!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.90,0:02:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing? You're going to make me fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.20,0:02:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.54,0:02:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should we do, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.97,0:02:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll keep bothering me till I stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.48,0:02:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Dad, I'll go get them to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.02,0:02:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're always fighting like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.55,0:02:58.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be over soon. Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.69,0:03:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like we were worried over nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.10,0:03:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.13,0:03:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.17,0:03:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.07,0:03:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.87,0:03:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you see where you're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.71,0:03:20.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later that day, we didn't feel comfortable about\Nwhat happened, so we went to check on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.68,0:03:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All evidence points to this being a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.69,0:03:33.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Estimated time of death is between 10 PM and 11 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.79,0:03:35.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.60,0:03:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.40,0:03:43.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bad things keep happening around you, Mouri-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.57,0:03:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.87,0:03:47.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's exactly as Mouri-san said.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.37,0:03:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to what the apartment owner said, there was\Na quarrel between our victim and another person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.25,0:03:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he tell you anything about the other person?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.85,0:04:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm, I-I'll ask right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.05,0:04:09.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even though you passed by this place,\Nyou couldn't stop this from happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.33,0:04:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, if it weren't for that old geezer, we would've\Nbeen able to stop this from happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.58,0:04:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,P-Please help me, Mouri-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.08,0:04:37.56,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Hiroshi Nakamoto (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.48,0:04:38.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takayoki Eri and I used to work together at\NBeika University. My name is Nakamoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.99,0:04:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nakamoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.19,0:04:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.83,0:04:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.89,0:04:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who killed Eri, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.73,0:04:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the police suspect me, I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.14,0:04:54.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night, I wasn't even home!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.44,0:04:55.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.64,0:05:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, we heard you arguing with him last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.05,0:05:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now you're telling us that you weren't home?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.79,0:05:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.55,0:05:10.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was on a tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.16,0:05:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That wasn't actually me! He used it to make\Npeople believe that I was in the apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.03,0:05:15.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.56,0:05:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He only did it to make a scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.23,0:05:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.00,0:05:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he closed the curtains, he played the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.74,0:05:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't throw things around!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.04,0:05:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pick it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.08,0:05:35.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,You want me to pick it up? You pick it up, you imbecile!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.62,0:05:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was making it all up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.88,0:05:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.02,0:05:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I don't have an alibi to prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.25,0:05:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.99,0:05:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why would he do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.66,0:05:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I could hide and spy on our professor,\Nwaiting for the chance to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.70,0:05:57.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.67,0:06:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was stealing our research results and claiming\Nthem as his own to gain fame among his peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.84,0:06:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although we knew what he was doing, there\Nwas nothing we could do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.42,0:06:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we... we decided to murder him and\Nmake it look like a random burglary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.16,0:06:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But I couldn't go through with it because,\Nwhen I went to his house, he wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.90,0:06:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I waited for him in his library for a long time,\Nbut eventually gave up and returned home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.27,0:06:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I arrived at the professor's house at 10 PM.\NBy the time I returned, it was 11 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.98,0:06:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If what you're saying is true, then you couldn't\Npossibly have committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.35,0:06:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday was my turn to watch the professor's house,\Nbut it seems that he was eating at a restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.76,0:06:57.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is really strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:07:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know why my professor would\Nlie about being home at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.00,0:07:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this goes any further, it's going to become embarrassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.01,0:07:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surely, the police will use that\Nto remove you from suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.71,0:07:17.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard from the investigators that Detective\NMouri-san was a witness to the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I decided to look for you. Please help me with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.09,0:07:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true I have encountered several similar cases, but—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.93,0:07:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew you wouldn't believe me when I told you, Mouri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.16,0:07:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that if we found the tape, you'd believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.07,0:07:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does such a thing even exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.77,0:07:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't find it back at our apartment, so it's\Npossible that the murderer took it with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.88,0:07:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I can't find that tape, then it'll be the end of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.45,0:07:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how can we find it? I'm sure the murderer\Nmust have dumped it by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.52,0:08:00.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad, shouldn't we try searching for the tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.99,0:08:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you are able to solve this case, surely you will improve\Nthe reputation of this agency! Right, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.93,0:08:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Improve our reputation? Yeah! Let's get that tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.74,0:08:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's start by searching near the\Napartment's entrances and exits.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.88,0:08:24.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now let's try near the train station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.08,0:08:30.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer would have tried to get\Nrid of the tape as fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.93,0:08:38.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you there! Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.87,0:08:43.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.90,0:08:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though he said that the murderer would have\Ngotten rid of the tape as fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:49.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.01,0:08:51.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! It's the tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.98,0:08:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finding this tape was a piece of cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.98,0:08:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for helping find this tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.55,0:09:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Takagi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.95,0:09:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be taking this as very important evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.39,0:09:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sure is a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.43,0:09:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One moment. I'll allow you to take\Nthe tape back to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.37,0:09:17.07,Signs,,0,0,0,,You want me to pick it up? You pick it up you imbecile!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.67,0:09:21.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is in fact the voice we heard\Nyesterday. Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.98,0:09:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.04,0:09:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This could prove that Nakamoto-kun was telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.38,0:09:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.75,0:09:38.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've finally found someone who believes what I\Nsaid. But why would the professor lie like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.32,0:09:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.89,0:09:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old geezer! If he hadn't lied, I wouldn't\Nhave been suspected in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.10,0:09:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.23,0:09:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The professor wants you out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.70,0:09:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.91,0:10:04.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that he was claiming\Nto be at home when he was not?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case then, it's possible that he's the real culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.36,0:10:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.06,0:10:15.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.73,0:10:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.60,0:10:26.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you suggesting the professor knew in\Nadvance of our plan to spy on his house?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.67,0:10:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that he was eavesdropping on us somehow?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.04,0:10:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eavesdropping—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.44,0:10:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, maybe that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.41,0:10:39.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, some of the screws are missing from this plug.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.48,0:10:41.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that he was listening in on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.85,0:10:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ahh, really? Thank you for your effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.69,0:10:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true. He was listening in on your phone calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.16,0:10:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's clear now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.43,0:10:57.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The professor was taking your research results and\Nclaiming them as his own for fame and fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.94,0:11:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Consequently, he was scared that you\Nwould want to take revenge on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.71,0:11:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That motivated him to monitor your phone calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.98,0:11:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was the one who tapped the\Nline. How'd he do it, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.68,0:11:17.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that while he was at the university,\Nhe used a copied key to break in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.72,0:11:20.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.29,0:11:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had been listening to your phone calls for awhile\Nand had discovered your plan to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.73,0:11:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a result, he used your own plan against you, twisted\Nit to fit his means, and created an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.47,0:11:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, last night, while the victim and Nakamoto\Nwere executing their plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.65,0:11:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the professor barged in unexpectedly and murdered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.49,0:11:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he took the tape from the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.49,0:12:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, when the body was found, of course\Nyou would be the first person suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.97,0:12:10.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thus, by killing him in a closed room, you would\Nundoubtedly be accused of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.38,0:12:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the professor's plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used our own plan against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.95,0:12:25.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, is that even with his devilish plan, he\Ndidn't expect to run into the famous Mouri Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.76,0:12:30.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey! Why do you always have to act like that, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.83,0:12:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You always end up being mistaken, waiting\Nfor me to swoop in and save the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.73,0:12:42.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you so happy? If you had listened to my advice\Nlast night, this murder never would have occurred!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.64,0:12:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.11,0:12:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I heard from Inspector Megure that you met\Nan old man with a dog last night on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.02,0:12:57.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! Had he not stepped in, things\Nwould have turned out differently!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.59,0:13:03.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, that man's intentions weren't bad, now were they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.06,0:13:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What if...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.47,0:13:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything makes sense now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.03,0:13:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle might have drank too much,\Nbut he was still doing his job!
Comment: 0,0:13:15.31,0:13:18.68,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Based off Manga
Comment: 0,0:13:15.31,0:13:18.68,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,None (Anime Original)
Comment: 0,0:13:15.31,0:13:18.68,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Original Air Date
Comment: 0,0:13:15.31,0:13:18.68,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,September 11th, 2000
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.48,0:13:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright. Let's go challenge Inspector Megure\Nand bet my reputation as a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.45,0:13:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.92,0:13:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? What's not good?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.52,0:13:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, I think we should wait for them to come to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.83,0:13:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to ask us what we were able to figure out, so that\Nwe can help them with their investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.60,0:13:42.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You might be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.33,0:13:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go plan a bit before they come.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.44,0:13:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying a premeditated murder and he has an alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.34,0:13:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Amazing deduction, Mouri-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.88,0:13:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.72,0:14:02.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You suspect the real culprit might be\Nyour professor. Right, Nakamoto-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.62,0:14:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.39,0:14:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My hate towards the professor has nothing to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.79,0:14:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we'll be checking that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.46,0:14:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi-kun! Get a warrant for the professor's arrest now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.17,0:14:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.04,0:14:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait a minute, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.78,0:14:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just thought of another possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.65,0:14:35.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know who the real killer is!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.79,0:14:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Real killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.36,0:14:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Mouri-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.73,0:14:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, please sit down and make yourself comfortable\Nso that I may explain everything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.00,0:14:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nakamoto-kun's story is nothing but a mere lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.94,0:14:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, there are two people that lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.17,0:15:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tape, however, remains an unchangeable fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While Nakamoto-kun was executing the plan to frame\Nhis college professor, he made a big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.13,0:15:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.53,0:15:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what you're trying to say is all his previous\Nstatements were meant to deceive us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.10,0:15:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's exactly what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.71,0:15:31.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, concerning the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.68,0:15:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how can we find it? I'm sure the murderer\Nmust have dumped it by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.08,0:15:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What Nakamoto-kun was doing was misleading\Nus into searching the trash for his tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.22,0:15:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That, and also...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.42,0:15:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old geezer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.63,0:15:52.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he hadn't lied, I wouldn't have been\Nsuspected in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.13,0:15:56.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what Nakamoto-kun said might be true. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:16:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that he was claiming\Nto be at home when he was not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.78,0:16:11.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that sentence, he created the\Npossibility of his professor's guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.32,0:16:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.29,0:16:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that he was eavesdropping on us somehow?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.76,0:16:21.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was, however, impossible to listen\Nin on their private conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.33,0:16:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to lead me into finding some\Nevidence proving his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.93,0:16:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While also placing the professor at the crime\Nscene at the time of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.87,0:16:39.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to use this information to\Nwarp my deductions for his own gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.71,0:16:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact is, these deductions came from one person,\Nand one person only. You, Nakamoto-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.58,0:16:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.39,0:16:53.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Needless to say, the culprit entered the victim's apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.79,0:17:00.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, as the victim was executing his\Ncharade, someone stabbed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.40,0:17:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.00,0:17:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit was living in the same apartment as the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.31,0:17:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a result, he did not need to tap the phone line.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.41,0:17:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you had to do was unscrew a couple of screws.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.52,0:17:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Nakamoto-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.29,0:17:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it strange since the beginning,\Nwhen we found the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.53,0:17:33.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was really thrown in the garbage after the murder, there\Nwould have been no way to find the tape when we did,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.00,0:17:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because the cans belong to a fast food restaurant\Nwhose garbage is picked up every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.51,0:17:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, the tape wasn't there to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.01,0:17:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That tape wasn't thrown away the night before,\Nyou threw it away just before I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.65,0:17:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you didn't throw it away then, I couldn't have\Nfound it. Isn't that right, Nakamoto-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.99,0:18:02.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying Mouri-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.03,0:18:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you're saying is crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.23,0:18:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.40,0:18:12.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Nakamoto-kun, but I have a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.94,0:18:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.78,0:18:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, Conan-kun asked me to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.21,0:18:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the one who sent him to bring you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.45,0:18:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, let's describe the one who was\Nplaying detective according to his plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he didn't have someone to help him play detective,\Nhe wouldn't have been able to complete his scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.40,0:18:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is why he thought of using someone as famous\Nas I, the Great Detective Mouri Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.00,0:18:49.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, he could not leave things to chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.24,0:18:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thus, he thought of a way to make me willingly talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.22,0:19:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.69,0:19:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He placed a flier in my mail box with an ad for an\Nall-you-can-eat food and drink special between 8 and 10 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.40,0:19:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! He knew Mouri-kun couldn't\Nresist such a tempting offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.70,0:19:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, he made sure that I would\Npass by the victim's apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.61,0:19:26.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And according to your timing,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.04,0:19:32.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our victim peeped through the window to make\Nsure I was there and then acted out his part.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.68,0:19:35.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, he had no idea he was getting himself killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.12,0:19:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was simply trying to make a scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.66,0:19:41.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did you say this lady is a witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.99,0:19:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.36,0:19:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nakamoto-kun, when someone placed\Nthat ad in my mailbox yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.83,0:19:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,this woman saw who that person was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.54,0:19:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Azuha-san, is this the person you\Nsaw put a flier in my mailbox yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.44,0:20:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.81,0:20:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, on my way to work, I saw\Nhim place a flier in your mailbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.08,0:20:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can identify the flier if I see it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.89,0:20:13.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course we'll be examining the flier,\Nand we will find your fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.49,0:20:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unlikely that the owner of that\Nrestaurant sent me this flier
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.23,0:20:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because it was only placed in my mailbox, Nakamoto-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.81,0:20:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's quite right. But what led you to suspect me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.45,0:20:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because of what you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.45,0:20:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I heard from Inspector Megure that you met\Nan old man with a dog last night on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.62,0:20:49.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I mentioned to the inspector that there\Nwas an old man who had forced me to leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.66,0:20:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did not mention him having a dog beside him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.83,0:20:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't have known that unless\Nyou were at the crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.31,0:21:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.37,0:21:08.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I had tried to stop that fight, your\Nplan would have been ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.75,0:21:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To prevent this, you intervened, stopping\Nme from interrupting the imaginary fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.15,0:21:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man with the dog, that was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.43,0:21:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You deserve the title "Great Detective." And\Nhere I thought detectives were fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.54,0:21:43.05,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Natsu no maboroshi
